    "summary": "This transition-metal-catalyzed cross-coupling reaction was performed using both homogeneous and heterogeneous catalysis in acetonitrile solvent with triethylamine as base. The flow process utilized an X-Cube Flash reactor with stainless steel tubing (1.0 mm ID, 4.0 mL volume) operated at 170°C with a 10-minute residence time and 0.4 mL/min flow rate under 10 bar back pressure. Both batch (150°C, 5 hours, microwave heating) and flow conditions achieved 94% yield at 0.65 M concentration. The flow process provided a significant time advantage, reducing reaction time from 5 hours to 10 minutes (30-fold acceleration) while allowing operation at higher temperature (170°C vs 150°C) and eliminating the need for microwave heating. The back pressure regulator was essential for maintaining single-phase liquid conditions at the elevated temperature.",
